**3. Platform API Details**

**3.1 TikTok Content Posting API**

  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  **Property**           **Details**

  Base URL               https://open.tiktokapis.com/v2/post/publish/

  Auth                   OAuth 2.0 Bearer Token (access_token per user)

  Upload Method          PULL_FROM_URL (preferred --- video already
                         hosted) or FILE_UPLOAD

  Scopes Required        video.publish, video.upload

  Rate Limit             30 requests/minute per user token

  Video Specs            MP4/MOV, H.264, AAC audio, 23-60 FPS, 9:16
                         aspect ratio

  Audit Requirement      Unaudited apps post in private mode. Must pass
                         TikTok audit for public.

  Domain Verification    Required for PULL_FROM_URL --- verify
                         corpfit.cloud in TT4D app
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------

**3.1.1 TikTok Publish Flow**

1.  POST /v2/post/publish/video/init/ with video_url and post_info
    (title, privacy, interaction settings)

2.  Receive publish_id from response

3.  Poll POST /v2/post/publish/status/fetch/ with publish_id until
    status = PUBLISH_COMPLETE

4.  Extract publicaly_available_post_id from response

5.  Store post_id and construct public URL in schedule_logs

**3.2 Instagram Graph API (Reels)**

  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  **Property**           **Details**

  Base URL               https://graph.facebook.com/v21.0/{ig-user-id}/

  Auth                   OAuth 2.0 via Facebook Login (long-lived page
                         token)

  Method                 2-step: Create container (POST /media) → Publish
                         (POST /media_publish)

  Scopes Required        instagram_basic, instagram_content_publish,
                         pages_read_engagement

  Account Type           Instagram Business or Creator account linked to
                         Facebook Page

  Video Specs            MP4/MOV, H.264, AAC, 9:16 aspect ratio, 5-90
                         seconds

  Processing             Container status polling required (FINISHED →
                         publish)

  Insights Available     GET /{ig-media-id}/insights --- reach, plays,
                         likes, saves, shares
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------

**3.2.1 Instagram Publish Flow**

1.  POST /{ig-user-id}/media with media_type=REELS, video_url, caption,
    share_to_feed=true

2.  Receive container_id (creation_id)

3.  Poll GET /{container_id}?fields=status_code until status = FINISHED

4.  POST /{ig-user-id}/media_publish with creation_id

5.  Receive media_id, construct permalink, store in schedule_logs

**3.3 LinkedIn Posts + Videos API**

  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  **Property**           **Details**

  Base URL               https://api.linkedin.com/rest/

  Auth                   OAuth 2.0 Bearer Token + Linkedin-Version header
                         (YYYYMM)

  Method                 3-step: Initialize upload → PUT video binary →
                         Create post

  Scopes Required        w_member_social (personal) or
                         w_organization_social (company page)

  Partner Program        Full Marketing API requires partner approval.
                         Basic posting works without.

  Video Specs            MP4, H.264, AAC, up to 10 minutes, max 5GB

  Analytics              Video Analytics API: views, time watched,
                         engagement (6-month window)
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------

**3.3.1 LinkedIn Publish Flow**

1.  POST /rest/videos?action=initializeUpload with owner URN and file
    size

2.  Receive uploadUrl and video URN from response

3.  PUT video binary to uploadUrl

4.  POST /rest/videos?action=finalizeUpload with video URN

5.  POST /rest/posts with video URN, commentary text, and visibility
    settings

6.  Receive post URN, store in schedule_logs

**4. Database Design**

**4.1 New Tables**

**4.1.1 schedule_logs**

Tracks every publish attempt across all platforms. One row per platform
per video.

  ----------------------- ------------- -------------- ------------------------------
  **Column**              **Type**      **Nullable**   **Description**

  **id**                  SERIAL PK     No             Auto-increment primary key

  **publish_log_id**      INTEGER FK    No             References publish_logs.id
                                                       (the video)

  **content_log_id**      INTEGER FK    No             References content_logs.id
                                                       (the content)

  **brief_id**            INTEGER FK    No             References briefs.id (original
                                                       brief)

  **platform**            VARCHAR(20)   No             tiktok \| instagram \|
                                                       linkedin

  **status**              VARCHAR(30)   No             queued \| uploading \|
                                                       processing \| live \| failed
                                                       \| held

  **platform_post_id**    TEXT          Yes            Native post ID from platform
                                                       API response

  **platform_post_url**   TEXT          Yes            Public URL of the live post

  **caption**             TEXT          Yes            Caption/description sent with
                                                       the post

  **hashtags**            TEXT          Yes            Hashtags included (JSON array)

  **scheduled_at**        TIMESTAMPTZ   Yes            When the post is/was scheduled
                                                       for

  **posted_at**           TIMESTAMPTZ   Yes            When the post actually went
                                                       live

  **error_message**       TEXT          Yes            Error details if status =
                                                       failed

  **retry_count**         INTEGER       No             Number of retry attempts
                                                       (default 0, max 3)

  **mode_used**           VARCHAR(10)   No             manual \| semi \| auto (which
                                                       mode triggered this)

  **operator_id**         TEXT          Yes            Telegram user ID of operator
                                                       who approved (manual mode)

  **created_at**          TIMESTAMPTZ   No             Row creation timestamp
                                                       (DEFAULT NOW())

  **updated_at**          TIMESTAMPTZ   No             Last update timestamp
  ----------------------- ------------- -------------- ------------------------------

**4.1.2 platform_accounts**

Stores OAuth credentials for each connected social platform account.

  ---------------------- -------------- -------------- ------------------------------
  **Column**             **Type**       **Nullable**   **Description**

  **id**                 SERIAL PK      No             Auto-increment primary key

  **platform**           VARCHAR(20)    No             tiktok \| instagram \|
                                                       linkedin

  **account_name**       VARCHAR(100)   No             Display name (e.g.,
                                                       \@corpfit_official)

  **account_id**         TEXT           No             Platform-specific account/user
                                                       ID

  **access_token**       TEXT           No             OAuth access token (encrypted
                                                       at rest)

  **refresh_token**      TEXT           Yes            OAuth refresh token for token
                                                       rotation

  **token_expires_at**   TIMESTAMPTZ    Yes            When the access token expires

  **is_active**          BOOLEAN        No             Whether this account is
                                                       enabled for posting (DEFAULT
                                                       true)

  **metadata**           JSONB          Yes            Platform-specific data
                                                       (page_id, ig_user_id, org_urn,
                                                       etc.)

  **created_at**         TIMESTAMPTZ    No             Row creation timestamp
  ---------------------- -------------- -------------- ------------------------------

**4.1.3 system_config**

Key-value store for system-wide settings including ORBIT scheduling
mode.

  ---------------- ------------- -------------- ------------------------------
  **Column**       **Type**      **Nullable**   **Description**

  **key**          VARCHAR(50)   No             Setting name (e.g.,
                   PK                           orbit_mode)

  **value**        TEXT          No             Setting value (e.g., manual)

  **updated_at**   TIMESTAMPTZ   No             Last modified timestamp
  ---------------- ------------- -------------- ------------------------------

Initial seed data for system_config:

-   orbit_mode = \'manual\' (default scheduling mode)

-   orbit_semi_delay_minutes = \'30\' (Semi-Auto hold window)

-   orbit_max_retries = \'3\' (max publish retry attempts)

-   orbit_platforms_enabled = \'tiktok,instagram,linkedin\' (active
    platforms)

**4.2 Indexes**

-   schedule_logs: (publish_log_id, platform) UNIQUE --- one post per
    platform per video

-   schedule_logs: (status) --- fast queued/failed lookups

-   schedule_logs: (platform, status) --- per-platform status queries

-   schedule_logs: (created_at DESC) --- dashboard recent posts

-   platform_accounts: (platform, is_active) --- active account lookups

