**7. Dashboard Updates**

**7.1 New Orbit Tab**

A new fifth tab added to the CorpFit Dashboard showing the publishing
pipeline status. This tab provides a mission-control view of all content
moving through ORBIT.

**7.1.1 Tab Sections**

-   **Queue Panel:** Videos waiting to be published. Shows video
    thumbnail, module, platforms, scheduled time. Actions: \[Launch
    Now\] \[Hold\] \[Cancel\]

-   **Live Panel:** Successfully published content. Shows platform icons
    with clickable links to live posts. Timestamp of when posted.

-   **Failed Panel:** Posts that failed with error details. Actions:
    \[Retry\] \[Skip\]. Error message and retry count visible.

-   **Stats Bar:** Top summary showing: Total Posted (24h) \| Queue Size
    \| Success Rate \| Mode indicator (red/yellow/green dot)

**7.1.2 Dashboard Actions**

  ------------------ ------------------ ----------------------------------
  **Button**         **API Action**     **Behavior**

  🚀 Launch Now      orbit_post         Immediately publish to selected
                                        platform(s)

  ⏸ Hold             orbit_hold         Cancel auto-launch timer, keep in
                                        queue

  🔄 Retry           orbit_retry        Re-attempt a failed publish

  ❌ Cancel          orbit_cancel       Remove from queue entirely, mark
                                        as cancelled

  ⚙ Mode             orbit_mode         Toggle between Manual/Semi/Auto
                                        (settings gear icon)
  ------------------ ------------------ ----------------------------------

**8. Platform Account Setup Guide**

CorpFit needs developer accounts on each platform before ORBIT can
publish. This section provides step-by-step setup instructions for each
platform.

**8.1 TikTok Developer Setup**

1.  Go to developers.tiktok.com and create a developer account

2.  Create a new app. Add products: \"Login Kit\" and \"Content Posting
    API\"

3.  Configure redirect URI:
    https://n8n.corpfit.cloud/rest/oauth2-credential/callback

4.  Request scopes: user.info.basic, video.publish, video.upload

5.  Verify domain ownership for corpfit.cloud in Manage URL Properties

6.  Test in Sandbox mode (posts will be private). Submit for audit to go
    public.

7.  Store Client Key and Client Secret in platform_accounts table

**8.2 Instagram / Meta Setup**

-   Create/convert Instagram account to Business or Creator type

-   Link Instagram account to a Facebook Page

-   Go to developers.facebook.com and create a Facebook App (type:
    Business)

-   Add products: Facebook Login + Instagram Graph API

-   Request permissions: instagram_basic, instagram_content_publish,
    pages_read_engagement

-   Generate long-lived Page Access Token (60 days, auto-refreshable)

-   Get Instagram Business Account ID via: GET
    /{page-id}?fields=instagram_business_account

-   Store access_token and ig_user_id in platform_accounts table

**8.3 LinkedIn Setup**

-   Create a LinkedIn Company Page for CorpFit (if not already existing)

-   Go to linkedin.com/developers and create an app associated with the
    Company Page

-   Request products: \"Share on LinkedIn\" and \"Sign In with LinkedIn
    using OpenID Connect\"

-   Verify Company Page in app settings

-   Request scope: w_member_social (personal) or w_organization_social
    (company page)

-   Generate OAuth 2.0 access token via 3-legged flow

-   Get organization URN: urn:li:organization:{company_id}

-   Store access_token and org URN in platform_accounts table

**9. Security Considerations**

-   **Token encryption:** All OAuth tokens stored in platform_accounts
    should be encrypted at rest. Use PostgreSQL pgcrypto extension or
    application-layer encryption.

-   **Token refresh:** Build automatic token refresh logic. TikTok
    tokens expire in 24h (refreshable), Instagram page tokens last 60
    days, LinkedIn tokens last 60 days.

-   **Rate limiting:** Implement per-platform rate limiting in the ORBIT
    Publisher. TikTok: 30 req/min. Instagram: 25 posts/24h. LinkedIn:
    150 posts/day.

-   **Error isolation:** A failure on one platform should never block
    publishing to others. Each platform call is independent.

-   **Audit logging:** Every publish attempt logged with full
    request/response metadata for debugging.

